---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Travel Information — Ramey & Hiba">
  <section class="section section--narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title">Arriving in Morocco</h2>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>
        When you arrive at the airport, we recommend taking out cash from an ATM before
        heading to your hotel or riad. Morocco uses Moroccan dirhams, and it is necessary
        to have cash on hand for taxis, tips, small shops, and local purchases. When using
        the ATM, decline any currency conversion offered on the screen. Choose to be
        charged in Moroccan dirhams instead, which usually helps avoid extra conversion
        fees from the ATM provider.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title">Driving &amp; Car Rentals</h2>

    <h3 class="section-subtitle">Driving in Morocco</h3>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>If you plan to rent a car, please keep these quick tips in mind before hitting the road.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <p class="tip__heading">Always buckle up</p>
      <p class="tip__body">
        Seatbelts are required and police may stop drivers or passengers who are not wearing one.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <p class="tip__heading">Yield at roundabouts</p>
      <p class="tip__body">
        Cars already in the roundabout have the right of way. Wait until you have clear space
        before entering.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="tip">
      <p class="tip__heading">Give yourself extra time</p>
      <p class="tip__body">
        Rabat is a busy city, and traffic can be heavy. Plan to leave a bit earlier than usual
        so you have plenty of time to arrive comfortably.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="margin-top: var(--space-section);">Car Rental Recommendations</h3>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>
        Renting a car is recommended for getting around Rabat during the wedding weekend, and
        it&rsquo;s also a wonderful way to explore more of Morocco while you&rsquo;re here.
        It&rsquo;s especially helpful for day trips, nearby cities, or turning the celebration
        into a little extra adventure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="recommendation">
      <p class="recommendation__label">Recommended</p>
      <a class="recommendation__link" href="https://www.kayak.com/cars" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        kayak.com/cars
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title">Getting Online</h2>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>
        We recommend setting up mobile data before you arrive so you can easily use maps,
        message other guests, and stay connected throughout the weekend.
      </p>
      <p>
        If your phone supports eSIMs, this is one of the easiest ways to have data ready as
        soon as you land in Morocco, making arrival day and getting around feel a little smoother.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="recommendation">
      <p class="recommendation__label">Recommended</p>
      <a class="recommendation__link" href="https://esims.io/countries/morocco" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        esims.io/countries/morocco
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
